<div class='intro row'>
  <div class='span6 offset3 header'>
    <h1>ActiveWarehouse</h1>
    <p>
      Ruby projects helping you to transform your data
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class='row span8 offset2 description'>
  <p>
    If you need to gather data from a system, adapt and transform it to reuse it in another app or a reporting system, you came at the right place.
  </p>
  <p>
    To get started, see:
    <ul>
      <li>the <a href="http://github.com/activewarehouse/activewarehouse-etl-sample">activewarehouse etl sample</a> which extracts, transforms and loads the Rails commit logs into a datawarehouse-like data structure,</li>
      <li>the partly obsolete but mostly useful <a href="https://github.com/activewarehouse/activewarehouse-etl/wiki/Documentation">etl manual</a></li>
    </ul>
  </p>
  <p>
    Any questions? Ask the <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/?fromgroups#!forum/activewarehouse-discuss">Google Group</a>!
  </p>
</div>

<div class='projects row'>
  <% @projects.each_with_index do |project, index| %>
    <div class='span6 offset3 section'>
      <% if index == 0 %>
      <% elsif index == 2 %>
        <p>The following projects are not up to date (but people use github forks in production):</p>
      <% end %>
    </div>

    <div class='project span6 offset3'>
      <h3><%= project.name %></h3>
      <p class='summary'>
        <%= project.summary %>
      </p>

      GitHub project:
      <a href="http://github.com/activewarehouse/<%= project.name %>">GitHub</a>
      <br/>

      Latest release: 
      <a href="https://rubygems.org/gems/<%= project.name %>/versions/<%= project.latest_version %>">
        <%= project.latest_version %>
        <%= project.published_at.strftime("%B %d, %Y") %>
      </a>

      <br/>

      <div class='status'>
        <a href="http://travis-ci.org/activewarehouse/<%= project.name %>"><img src="https://secure.travis-ci.org/activewarehouse/<%= project.name %>.png?branch=master" alt="Build Status" ></img></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  <% end %>
</div>

<div class='row'>
  <footer class='span8 offset2'>
    ActiveWarehouse is currently maintained by <a href="http://twitter.com/thibaut_barrere">Thibaut Barr√®re</a>.
  </footer>
</div>